<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1003,1316]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1184,1208]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Note.</emphasis>
The structure of the arista is much more like that of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Nartshuk 1959: 472" authorityName="Nartshuk" authorityPageNumber="472" authorityYear="1959" box="[971,1380,1183,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephalisca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1150,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Platycephalisca</emphasis>
Nartshuk 1959: 472
</taxonomicName>
than that of 
<emphasis box="[232,385,1219,1244]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1858" box="[232,380,1219,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Pachylophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachylophus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The short head and absence of a prominent facial carina excludes its inclusion in the former genus. The 
<typeStatus box="[279,375,1256,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">paratype</typeStatus>
has the postpedicel dirty yellow on all but a dorsal line, the first aristal segment slightly shorter and the anepisternum dusted only in upper posterior corner.
</paragraph>
